Red Arrows Crash Reports Being Investigated, U.K. Ministry Says

-- B y   J o h n   G l o v e r
-- 
2011-08-20T13:46:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-20/red-arrows-crash-reports-being-investigated-u-k-ministry-says.html
The U.K.’s Ministry of Defence said
it’s investigating reports that a plane belonging to the Royal
Air Force’s Red Arrows aerobatics display team has crashed in
southern  England .  The ministry is aware of an incident today and is
investigating, said a spokesman, declining be named in line with
ministry policy.  The plane crashed near the coastal town of Bournemouth,
where an air show is being held today, Sky News and the British
Broadcasting Corp. reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Glover in London at 
 johnglover@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Armstrong at 
 Parmstrong10@bloomberg.net  